ronauts: The Memoirs of Major General Benjamin D. Foulois''. New York: McGraw-Hill Book Company.\n*{{cite book| author=Futrell, Robert F.| chapter= | title=Ideas, Concepts, Doctrine: Basic Thinking in the United States Air Force 1907\u20131960, Vol. I | editor=| publisher=Air University Press|isbn= 1-58566-029-9| year=1989}}\n*{{cite web| last =Futrell| first =Robert F| year =1951| url =http://www.afhra.af.mil/shared/media/document/AFD-090601-058.pdf| title =Development of AAF Base Facilities in the United States 1939\u20131945| publisher =Air Force Historical Research Agency| accessdate =15 January 2011| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20120908061635/http://www.afhra.af.mil/shared/media/document/AFD-090601-058.pdf| archive-date =8 September 2012| url-status =dead| df =dmy-all}}\n*Greenfield, Col. Kent Roberts (1948). Study No. 35 ''Army Ground Forces and the Air-Ground Battle Team''. Historical Section Army Ground Forces, AD-A954 913\n*{{cite book |last=Greer |first=Thomas H. |year=1985 |title=The Development of Air Doctrine in the Army Air Arm, 1917\u20131941 |publisher=(USAF Historical Study 89). Center For Air Force History |location=[[Maxwell Air Force Base]] |url=http://www.afhra.af.mil/shared/media/document/AFD-090601-130.pdf |accessdate=10 November 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313132536/http://www.afhra.af.mil/shared/media/document/AFD-090601-130.pdf |archive-date=13 March 2013 |url-status=dead  }}\n*{{cite book |last=Griffith |first=  Charles |year=1999 |title=The Quest: Haywood Hansell and American Strategic Bombing in World War II |publisher=Air University Press |location=[[Maxwell Air Force Base]] |accessdate =|isbn=1-58566-069-8 }}\n*Maurer, Maurer (1987). ''Aviation in the U.S. Army, 1919\u20131939'', Office of Air Force History, Washington, D.C. {{ISBN|1-4102-1391-9}}\n*Maurer, Maurer (1961). ''[http://media.defense.gov/2010/Sep/21/2001330256/-1/-1/0/AFD-100921-044.pdf Air Force Combat Units of World War II]'', Office of