est Ensemble Cast {{small|(shared with the cast)}}\n| <center>''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]''</center>\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Huntington-Whiteley baronets]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Rankin Photography: ''Ten Times Rosie''. London: The Full Service, 2010. {{ISBN|978-0-9563-1555-7}}.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{IMDb name|2492819}}\n* [http://www.burkespeerage.com/ Rosie Huntington-Whiteley @ Burke's Peerage & Baronetage]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120903151007/http://eliteny.themode.net/div/elite/model/rosiehuntingtonwhitely/p/284/c/-1/?page=1 Rosie Huntington-Whiteley @ Elite New York City]\n\n{{Victoria's Secret Angels}}\n{{2000-2009VSFashion Show}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huntington-Whiteley, Rosie}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Tavistock]]\n[[Category:People connected with Tavistock]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Devon]]\n[[Category:English people of Polish-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:English female models]]\n[[Category:English film actresses]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:21st-century English actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Beverly Hills, California]]\n[[Category:English people of Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:Whiteley family|Rosie]]\n[[Category:Victoria's Secret Angels]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English model and actress}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2012}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name          = Rosie Huntington-Whiteley\n| image         = File:Paris Motor Show 2014 - Land Rover Discovery Sport 23 (cropped).jpg\n| caption       = Huntington-Whiteley in October 2014\n|birth_name     = Rosie Alice Huntington-Whiteley\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1987|4|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Plymouth]], [[Devon]], [[England]]\n| nationality   = British\n| partner       = [[Jason Statham]] <br>{{small|(2010\u2013present; engaged)}}\n| children      = 1\n| agency        = [[Creative Artists Agency|CAA]] (New York, Los Angeles)\n| hair_colour   = Blonde\n| eye_colour    = Blue\n| height        = {{height|m=1.75}}\n| occupation    = {{Flatlist|\n* Model\n* actress\n* fashion designer\n* businesswoman<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/culture/events/news/a38473/video-watch-rosie-huntington-whiteley/|title=VIDEO: Watch Rosie Huntington-Whiteley and Elizabeth Hurley bond over business|last=Alexander|first=Ellas|date=2 November 2016|website=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312060556/http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/culture/events/news/a38473/video-watch-rosie-huntington-whiteley/|archive-date=12 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> }}\n}}\n\n'''Rosie Alice Huntington-Whiteley'''<ref name=\"GQ UK\"/> (born 18 April 1987)<ref name=express /> is an [[English people|English]] model, actress, designer, and businesswoman. She is best known for her work for lingerie retailer [[Victoria's Secret]], formerly being one of their brand \"Angels\", for being the face of [[Burberry]]'s 2011 brand fragrance \"Burberry Body\", for her work with [[Marks & Spencer]], and, most recently, for her artistic collaboration with denim-focused fashion brand Paige.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=http://www.vogue.com/13493165/rosie-huntington-paige-denim-collaboration-exclusive/|title=Has Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Designed the Perfect Model Off-Duty Jeans?|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=18 October 2016|language=en-US|access-date=2016-10-19|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019211552/http://www.vogue.com/13493165/rosie-huntington-paige-denim-collaboration-exclusive/|archive-date=19 October 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nMoving into acting, she became known for her supporting roles as [[Carly Witwicky#Transformers Cinematic Universe|Carly Spencer]] in the 2011 film ''[[Transformers: Dark of the Moon]]'', the third installment in the [[Transformers (film series)|''Transformers'' film series]],<ref name=\"Transformers3\"/> and as The Splendid Angharad in the 2015 film ''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]''.<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.businessinsider.com/mad-max-fury-road-wives-rosie-huntington-whiteley-riley-keough-zoe-kravitz-2015-5|title=Here's what the stunning 'Mad Max' wives look like in real life|last=Acuna|first=Kirsten|work=Business Insider|date=17 May 2015|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nHuntington-Whiteley was born in [[Plymouth, Devon]],<ref name=express /> the daughter of Fiona (''n\u00e9e'' Jackson), a fitness instructor, and Charles, a [[Chartered Surveyor|chartered surveyor]].<ref name=ad1>{{Cite news|last=Fulton|first=Rick|title=Rosie Huntington Whiteley: I may be the world's sexiest woman, but I didn't get this body by accident|newspaper=Daily Record|date=17 June 2011|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/editors-choice/2011/06/17/rosie-huntington-whiteley-i-may-be-the-world-s-sexiest-woman-but-i-didn-t-get-this-body-by-accident-86908-23207355/|accessdate=29 June 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110623174941/http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/editors-choice/2011/06/17/rosie-huntington-whiteley-i-may-be-the-world-s-sexiest-woman-but-i-didn-t-get-this-body-by-accident-86908-23207355/|archivedate=23 June 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She has a brother and a sister.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/photos/8174/stars-sexy-siblings/471311|title=Rosie and Toby Huntington-Whiteley from Stars' Sexy Siblings|work=E! Online|access-date=2018-04-17|language=en-US}}</ref> She grew up on a farm near [[Tavistock, Devon]].<ref name=express>{{cite news| url=http://www.express.co.uk/posts/view/245241/Is-this-the-sexiest-woman-in-the-world-| newspaper=[[Daily Express]] | location = UK| title=Is this the Sexiest Woman in the World?|first=Anna| last=Pukas| date=7 May 2011| accessdate=13 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| url=http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-news/529221/transformers-star-rosie-huntington-whiteley-i-m-not-posh-i-grew-up-with-pigs-and-sheep| journal=Now Magazine| title=Transformers Star Rosie Huntington-Whiteley: I'm not posh, I grew up with pigs and sheep| date=4 July 2011| accessdate=13 July 2015| url-status=live| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150513011813/http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-news/529221/transformers-star-rosie-huntington-whiteley-i-m-not-posh-i-grew-up-with-pigs-and-sheep| archivedate=13 May 2015| df=dmy-all}}</ref> She is a member of a [[Huntington-Whiteley baronets|noble family]] as her paternal great-grandfather, Wing-Commander Eric Huntington-Whiteley JP, was the nephew of [[George Whiteley, 1st Baron Marchamley]] and the younger son of politician [[Sir Herbert Huntington-Whiteley, 1st Baronet]]; Eric's wife, Rosie's great-grandmother, Enid Kohn, was from a family of [[Polish Jews]] who emigrated to England in the 1870s.{{cn|date=November 2019}} Rosie's paternal grandmother, Gillian, also from a [[Jewish]] family, was the daughter of Jacob Franks, a prominent surgeon in Sussex.<ref name=teo>{{Cite book|title=Debrett's peerage and baronetage|publisher=Kelly's Directories|year=1976|pages=2129|url=|id=}}</ref>\n\nEducated at [[Tavistock College]], she later revealed that she was bullied and teased at school for having a double-barrelled name, small breasts and full lips.<ref name=\"GQ UK\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/girls/articles/2011-05/23/gq-girls-rosie-huntington-whiteley/interview-photos|title=When GQ met Rosie|last=Mills|first=Simon|date=25 May 2011|journal=[[GQ]]|accessdate=8 June 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110527235221/http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/girls/articles/2011-05/23/gq-girls-rosie-huntington-whiteley/interview-photos|archivedate=27 May 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/05/31/rosie-huntington-whiteley-childhood-bullying|title=Lippy Girls|last=Alexander|first=Ella|date=31 May 2011|journal=[[Vogue UK]]|accessdate=8 June 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629235159/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/05/31/rosie-huntington-whiteley-childhood-bullying|archivedate=29 June 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She used to smoke, as she said in an interview with David Letterman: <blockquote>\"I got a work placement at a modelling agency and then I spent the week making coffee and picking up the telephone and smoking cigarettes and drinking wine at 11 AM, it was very ''[[Absolutely Fabulous|Ab Fab]]''\".</blockquote>She last publicly smoked in 2012 and has since quit.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/clean-living-stars-who-been-7568447|title=The clean-living celebs who are secret smokers|last=Moon|first=Rachael|date=2016-03-16|work=mirror|access-date=2018-02-08}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Modelling ===\nWhile a 15-year-old student, she undertook [[work experience]] at [[West End of London|London West End]]-based model agency Profile, before taking her [[GCSE]]s.<ref name=\"TiP12696409\">{{cite news|url=http://www.plymouthherald.co.uk/m-luckiest-girl-says-model-Rosie/story-12696409-detail/story.html|last=This Is Plymouth|title=I'm the luckiest girl|newspaper=Plymouth Herald|date=26 July 2008|accessdate=12 November 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103234059/http://www.plymouthherald.co.uk/m-luckiest-girl-says-model-Rosie/story-12696409-detail/story.html|archivedate=3 November 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Signed after leaving school in summer 2003 aged 16, her first modelling session was for a Levi's jeans commercial.<ref name=\"GQ UK\"/> She got her first big break in January 2004 when she travelled to [[New York City]] for a shoot with ''[[Teen Vogue]]''.<ref name=TiP12696409/> She later made her catwalk d\u00e9but alongside [[Naomi Campbell]] in New York City in Spring 2004,<ref name=\"TiP12696409\" /> and was then photographed by [[Bruce Weber (photographer)|Bruce Weber]] for [[Abercrombie & Fitch]].<ref name=\"NYmag\">{{cite journal|url=http://nymag.com/fashion/models/rhuntington/rosiehuntington/|title=Model Profile - Rosie Huntington|journal=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=27 October 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106074434/http://nymag.com/fashion/models/rhuntington/rosiehuntington/|archivedate=6 November 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2006, she was signed to American lingerie brand [[Victoria's Secret]], making her d\u00e9but at the brand's fashion show in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley|url=http://www.vogue.com.au/celebrity/models/rosie+huntington+whiteley,45|website=Vogue.com.au|accessdate=11 August 2017|date=27 May 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811191353/http://www.vogue.com.au/celebrity/models/rosie+huntington+whiteley,45|archive-date=11 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Victoria's Secret: From 1995 To 2016|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/victorias-secret-show-archive-past-catwalks|website=www.vogue.co.uk|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:RosieHuntington-WhiteleyJun2011.jpg|thumb|upright|left|At the ''[[Transformers: Dark of the Moon]]'' premiere in June 2011]]\n\nHuntington-Whiteley remained unknown outside the fashion industry until 2008, when she was cast by chief creative director [[Christopher Bailey (fashion designer)|Christopher Bailey]], replacing [[Agyness Deyn]] for [[Burberry]]'s autumn/winter campaign with actor [[Sam Riley]].<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2008/07/meet_the_new_girl_rosie_huntin.html|title=Meet the New Girl: Rosie Huntington|last=Lim|first=James|date=7 July 2008|journal=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100219060409/http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2008/07/meet_the_new_girl_rosie_huntin.html|archivedate=19 February 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2008/06/burberrys_new_deynless_fall_ad_1.html|title=Burberry's New Deyn-less Fall Ads|date=27 June 2008|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100219061011/http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2008/06/burberrys_new_deynless_fall_ad_1.html|archivedate=19 February 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She got her first ''[[British Vogue]]'' cover on the November 2008 issue, alongside Eden Clark and [[Jourdan Dunn]] in a feature celebrating British models.<ref name=\"NYmag\" /><ref>{{cite web| url=http://models.com/work/british-vogue-november-2008| publisher=Models.com| title=British Vogue cover - Nov 2008| accessdate=13 July 2015| url-status=live| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714090856/http://models.com/work/british-vogue-november-2008| archivedate=14 July 2015| df=dmy-all}}</ref> The following year, she was featured as the face of [[Karen Millen]]'s spring/summer 2009 advertising campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.karenmillen.com/2009/01/22/rosie-fronts-new-campaign/|title=Rosie fronts new campaign|last=Millen|first=Karen|date=22 January 2009|publisher=karenmillen.com|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110812151658/http://blog.karenmillen.com/2009/01/22/rosie-fronts-new-campaign/|archivedate=12 August 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She starred in a short film for Agent Provocateur lingerie playing a woman whose boyfriend forgets Valentine's Day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fashiontv.com/news/rosie-huntington-whiteleys-sexiest-moments-ever_2223.html |publisher=FashionTV |title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley's Sexiest Moments Ever |date=18 August 2014 |accessdate=13 July 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714095031/http://www.fashiontv.com/news/rosie-huntington-whiteleys-sexiest-moments-ever_2223.html |archivedate=14 July 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nFor fall/winter 2009, she modelled in campaigns for [[Godiva Chocolatier|Godiva]] and Miss Sixty.<ref name=\"advertising\"/> In February 2010, Huntington-Whiteley officially became a [[Victoria's Secret#Victoria's Secret Angels|Victoria's Secret Angel]]<ref>https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/rosie-huntington-whiteley-becomes-a-victorias-secret-angel</ref> modelling for the [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]] in New York City.<ref name=\"T\">{{cite news|url=http://women.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/women/fashion/article6957305.ece?token=null&offset=0&page=1|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley: Let's get saucy|last=Ings-Chambers|first=Edwina|date=20 December 2009|work=The Sunday Times |location=UK |accessdate=30 April 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, she posed nude for the [[Pirelli Calendar]], which was photographed by [[Terry Richardson]].<ref name=\"T\"/> Huntington-Whiteley hit the runway for designers [[Prada]] in [[Milan Fashion Week|Milan]] and [[Giles Deacon]] in [[Paris Fashion Week|Paris]].<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/02/the_prada_show_was_all_about_b.html|title=The Prada Show Was All About Boobs|last=Odell|first=Amy|date=25 February 2010|journal=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810194224/http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/02/the_prada_show_was_all_about_b.html|archivedate=10 August 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/03/highlights_from_giles_victoria.html|title=Highlights From Giles: Victoria's Secret Models and a Bag With Eyes|last=Odell|first=Amy|date=4 March 2010|journal=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120614061446/http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/03/highlights_from_giles_victoria.html|archivedate=14 June 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> For SS10 her advertising campaigns included Monsoon's first underwear line, Thomas Wylde, [[Full Circle (fashion)|Full Circle]], and [[Victoria's Secret|VS Online]].<ref name=\"advertising\">{{cite web|url=http://models.com/models/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley/year/advertising|publisher=Models.com|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley - Advertising|accessdate=13 July 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714073535/http://models.com/models/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley/year/advertising|archivedate=14 July 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In March, she collaborated with VOGUE.COM to share her outfit choices daily for the ''Today I'm Wearing'' feature.<ref>{{cite journal| url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2010/03/03/rosie-huntington-whiteley| journal=Vogue| title=Coming Up Rosie| last=Milligan| first=Lauren| date=3 March 2010| accessdate=13 July 2015| url-status=live| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714073451/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2010/03/03/rosie-huntington-whiteley| archivedate=14 July 2015| df=dmy-all}}</ref> She appeared on the covers of the May 2010 issues of ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'' Russia and ''[[GQ]]'' UK.<ref name=\"magazine covers\">{{cite web|url=http://models.com/models/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley/year/magazine|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley \u2013 Magazine Covers|publisher=Models.com|accessdate=13 July 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714094422/http://models.com/models/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley/year/magazine|archivedate=14 July 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She was featured on the cover of ''[[LOVE (magazine)|LOVE]]'' Magazine's September issue, styled as a [[pinup girl]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/08/love_mag.html|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Plays a Hot Pinup Girl on Love's September Cover|last=Vilensky|first=Mike|date=2 August 2010|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100806193519/http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/08/love_mag.html|archivedate=6 August 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref> For [[Fashion week|FW10]] she modelled for [[Burberry]] as well as the company's first Beauty line;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.instyle.com/2010/07/08/burberry-beautys-fall-ad-campaign/|title=Burberry Beauty's First Ad Campaign Revealed|last=Jacoby|first=Rachel|date=8 July 2010|publisher=In Style|accessdate=5 June 2011}}</ref> her other advertising campaigns included Thomas Wylde and [[Leon Max]].<ref name=\"advertising\" /><ref>{{cite journal| url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/beauty/news/100423-new-burberry-prorsum-beauty-line.aspx| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100501185509/http://www.vogue.co.uk/beauty/news/100423-new-burberry-prorsum-beauty-line.aspx| url-status=dead| archive-date=1 May 2010| journal=Vogue| title=Burberry Beauty| last=Forrester| first=Sharon| date=23 April 2010| accessdate=26 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nFashion photographer [[Rankin (photographer)|Rankin]] devoted a book entirely to her entitled ''Ten Times Rosie''. Rankin opined that Huntington-Whiteley brought something different to modelling: \"We\u2019ve been looking at very, very skinny, almost masculine girls for a long time. [Rosie] really is the model of the moment. She\u2019s the actress of the moment. She\u2019s definitely going to become something much, much bigger.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/09/to_rosie_huntington-whitely_mi.html|title=To Rosie Huntington-Whitely, Missing Her Book Party Is Like Missing the Oscars|date=22 September 2010|last=Hutchinson|first=Kate|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=30 April 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710041608/http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2010/09/to_rosie_huntington-whitely_mi.html|archivedate=10 July 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Celebrity make-up artist [[Ruby Hammer]], who has worked with Huntington-Whiteley for years, described her as the \"quintessential\" [[Wiktionary:English rose|English rose]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.express.co.uk/posts/view/198046/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley:-Is-model-nice-girl-Rosie%60s-transformation-complete |title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley: Is Model Nice Girl Rosie's Transformation Complete?| newspaper=Daily Express| first=Lesley-Ann |last=Jones |date=7 September 2010| accessdate=23 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2011, Huntington-Whiteley landed her first solo ''[[British Vogue]]'' cover<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/daily/110131-rosie-huntingtonwhiteley-march-vog.aspx|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110201135721/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/daily/110131-rosie-huntingtonwhiteley-march-vog.aspx|url-status=dead|archive-date=1 February 2011|title=March On|date=1 February 2011|last=Milligan|first=Lauren|publisher=[[Vogue UK]]|accessdate=30 April 2011}}</ref> and appeared on the covers of the UK's July issues of ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' and ''[[GQ]]''.<ref name=\"magazine covers\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG8539599/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley-I-was-told-I-had-to-get-into-better-shape.html|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley: 'I was told I had to get into better shape'|last=Bergin|first=Olivia|date=26 May 2011|publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|accessdate=5 June 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110530000632/http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG8539599/Rosie-Huntington-Whiteley-I-was-told-I-had-to-get-into-better-shape.html|archivedate=30 May 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She was unveiled as the face of [[Burberry]]'s newest fragrance, Burberry Body, in July 2011.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG8716408/Sample-Burberrys-new-Body-scent-via-Facebook.html| title=Sample Burberry's new Body scent via Facebook| newspaper=The Telegraph| first=Kate| last=Shapland| date=22 August 2011| accessdate=23 August 2011| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110831000852/http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG8716408/Sample-Burberrys-new-Body-scent-via-Facebook.html| archivedate=31 August 2011| df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| url=http://www.instyle.co.uk/news/first-look-rosie-huntington-whiteley-as-the-face-of-burberry-body-fragrance-13-07-11| title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley as the face of Burberry Body fragrance| journal=InStyle| date=13 July 2011| accessdate=23 August 2011| url-status=live| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110816073521/http://www.instyle.co.uk/news/first-look-rosie-huntington-whiteley-as-the-face-of-burberry-body-fragrance-13-07-11| archivedate=16 August 2011| df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2013, Huntington-Whiteley starred alongside [[Helena Bonham Carter]] and [[David Gandy]] in the [[Marks & Spencer]] Christmas advert.<ref>{{cite journal| url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2013/11/05/marks--spencer-christmas-film-starring-rosie-huntington-whiteley| journal=Vogue (UK)| title=Marks & Spencer's Christmas Fairy Tale| accessdate=6 December 2013| url-status=live| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212081920/http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2013/11/05/marks--spencer-christmas-film-starring-rosie-huntington-whiteley| archivedate=12 December 2013| df=dmy-all}}</ref> She was also announced as the face of Australian cosmetics brand [[ModelCo]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.modelcocosmetics.com/rosie-for-modelco/the-new-face-of-modelco-rosie-huntington-whiteley/| publisher=Modelco Cosmetics| title=The New Face of ModelCo: Rosie Huntington-Whiteley| accessdate=15 July 2015| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716081424/http://www.modelcocosmetics.com/rosie-for-modelco/the-new-face-of-modelco-rosie-huntington-whiteley/| archivedate=16 July 2015| df=dmy-all}}</ref>  In 2014, PAIGE announced Huntington-Whiteley as their ambassador for their upcoming Spring 2015 ad campaign.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/rosie-huntington-whiteley-paige-collaboration-collection|title=Rosie Turns Denim Designer?|last=Milligan|first=Lauren|newspaper=British Vogue|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-10-12|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012152710/http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/rosie-huntington-whiteley-paige-collaboration-collection|archivedate=12 October 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In February 2017, PAIGE launched their first ever design collaboration with Huntington-Whiteley on a 17 piece capsule collection for Spring called Rosie HW x PAIGE.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/rosie-huntington-paige-denim-collaboration-exclusive|title=Has Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Designed the Perfect Model Off-Duty Jeans?|work=Vogue|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paige.com/rosiehw-paige-collaboration-lookbook|title=ROSIE HW X PAIGE COLLECTION|website=www.paige.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-05}}</ref> This was followed by a Fall collection consisting of 20 pieces.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/paige-turner-rosie-huntington-whitley-and-paige-adams-geller-collaborate-on-collection-10971444/|title=Paige-Turner: Rosie Huntington-Whitley and Paige Adams-Geller Collaborate on Collection|last=Medina|first=Marcy|date=2017-09-06|work=WWD|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nShe has walked the runways for [[Givenchy]], [[Burberry]], [[Oscar De La Renta]], [[Valentino SpA|Valentino]], [[Michael Kors]], [[Roberto Cavalli]], [[Balmain (fashion house)|Balmain]], [[Louis Vuitton]], [[DSquared2]], [[Badgley Mischka]], [[Blumarine]], [[Marchesa]], [[Vivienne Tam]], [[Versace]], [[Vera Wang]], [[Betsey Johnson]], [[Alberta Ferretti]], [[Prada]], [[Giles Deacon]], and [[Moschino]].\n\nShe has appeared in advertising campaigns for [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Burberry]], [[Nirav Modi]], [[Ralph Lauren]], [[DKNY]], [[Escada]], [[Versace]], [[Leon Max]], [[Prabal Gurung]], [[Balmain (fashion house)|Balmain]], [[Karen Millen]], [[Loewe, S.A.|Loewe]], [[Bvlgari]], [[Tommy Hilfiger]], [[Max Azria|BCBG]], [[Thomas Wylde]], [[Clinique]], [[Sportmax]], [[Topshop]], [[Marks & Spencer]], [[Victoria's Secret]], [[French Connection (clothing)|French Connection]], [[Levi's]], [[Macy's]], and [[Bloomingdale's]].\n\n===Acting===\nIn May 2010, it was announced that Huntington-Whiteley would become the new female lead in ''[[Transformers: Dark of the Moon]]'', released 29 June 2011, replacing [[Megan Fox]].<ref name=\"Transformers3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1640047/20100526/story.jhtml |title=Model Rosie Huntington-Whiteley To Replace Megan Fox In |work=MTV |date=26 May 2010 |accessdate=26 May 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100527201915/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1640047/20100526/story.jhtml |archivedate=27 May 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She had previously worked with the film's director, [[Michael Bay]], on a Victoria's Secret commercial.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michaelbay.com/blog/files/6648dbac8d77a46d69a3e9f74e72051d-664.php|title=On the Set: Michael Bay Prepares the New Model 'Transformers'|date=1 May 2011|publisher=Michael Bay web site|accessdate=16 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120906103307/http://www.michaelbay.com/blog/files/6648dbac8d77a46d69a3e9f74e72051d-664.php|archivedate=6 September 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[MTV Networks]]' NextMovie.com named her one of the \"Breakout Stars to Watch for in 2011\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nextmovie.com/blog/breakout-movie-stars-of-2011/|title=25 Breakout Stars to Watch for in 2011|last=Evry|first=Max|date=5 January 2011|publisher=Next Movie|accessdate=10 April 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110308082919/http://www.nextmovie.com/blog/breakout-movie-stars-of-2011/|archivedate=8 March 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Prior to the film's release, she won the \"Female Star of Tomorrow\" award at the 2011 CinemaCon Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/girls/2011/04/rosie-huntington-whiteley-wins-female-star-of-tomorrow-at-cinemacon|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Wins \"Female Star of Tomorrow\" At CinemaCon|last=Cantor|first=Paul|date=1 April 2011|publisher=Complex|accessdate=5 June 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110412073737/http://www.complex.com/girls/2011/04/rosie-huntington-whiteley-wins-female-star-of-tomorrow-at-cinemacon|archivedate=12 April 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nReviewers were critical of the acting of Huntington-Whiteley and co-star [[Shia LaBeouf]]. [[Peter Travers]] (of [[Wenner Media]]) stated the two \"couldn't be duller\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Transformers: Dark of the Moon |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/transformers-dark-of-the-moon-20110629 |author=Travers, Peter |authorlink=Peter Travers |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=Wenner Media |date=29 June 2011 |accessdate=4 July 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703031426/http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/transformers-dark-of-the-moon-20110629 |archivedate=3 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Jason Solomons of ''The Observer'' wrote that \"we're first introduced to Rosie via a close-up of her bum, segueing straight from the film's opening sequence and titles on to the pert buttocks and underwear of our heroine\", and that Huntington-Whiteley's English posh girl accent \"renders her practically unintelligible when surrounded by American accents and falling masonry\".<ref name=Solomons>{{cite news|last=Solomons|first=Jason|title=Transformers: Dark of the Moon \u2013 review|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/jul/03/transformers-3-dark-moon-review|accessdate=30 April 2012|newspaper=The Observer|date=2 July 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131204161608/http://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/jul/03/transformers-3-dark-moon-review|archivedate=4 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Much of the criticism towards Rosie Huntington-Whiteley compared her in an unfavorable light to Megan Fox. [[Lou Lumenick]] said that her \"'acting' makes...Megan Fox look like [[Meryl Streep]] in comparison\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Total bomb! |url=http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/movies/total_bomb_EytV7DoJnE6e4UTuDyqi6N?CMP=OTC-rss&FEEDNAME= |author=Lumenick, Lou |authorlink=Lou Lumenick |work=[[New York Post]] |publisher=[[News Corporation (1980\u20132013)|News Corporation]] |date=29 June 2011 |accessdate=4 July 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703230042/http://www.nypost.com/p/entertainment/movies/total_bomb_EytV7DoJnE6e4UTuDyqi6N?CMP=OTC-rss&FEEDNAME= |archivedate=3 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In a positive review, [[Drew McWeeny]] of [[HitFix]] said, \"She reminds me of [[Cameron Diaz]] in ''[[The Mask (1994 film)|The Mask]]'', an actress who doesn't really show off any range, but who gives a natural, winning performance and who is up to the challenge of this particular picture.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/motion-captured/posts/review-transformers-dark-of-the-moon-wraps-up-with-the-best-of-the-franchise|title=Review: 'Transformers: Dark Of The Moon' wraps up with the best of the franchise|date=27 June 2011|first=Drew|last=McWeeny|accessdate=16 July 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704052202/http://www.hitfix.com/blogs/motion-captured/posts/review-transformers-dark-of-the-moon-wraps-up-with-the-best-of-the-franchise|archivedate=4 July 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHuntington-Whiteley had her second acting role in the film ''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]'', which was released in May 2015. She played The Splendid Angharad, one of the Five Wives of the warlord [[Immortan Joe]]. In order to portray her pregnant character, she wore a prosthetic stomach throughout the film.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/05/16/friday-box-office-mad-max-fury-road-races-to-16-8m/|title= Friday Box Office: 'Mad Max: Fury Road' Races To $16.8M|author= Scott Mendelson|work= [[Forbes]]|publisher= Forbes, Inc.|date= 16 May 2015|accessdate= 22 May 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150521064335/http://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/05/16/friday-box-office-mad-max-fury-road-races-to-16-8m/|archivedate= 21 May 2015|df= dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.vogue.com/13260722/rosie-huntington-whiteley-mad-max-fury-road/|title= How Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Breaks the Model-Turned-Actress Mold In Mad Max: Fury Road|author= Liana Satenstein|work= [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|publisher= [[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]|date= 13 May 2015|accessdate= 22 May 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150521170811/http://www.vogue.com/13260722/rosie-huntington-whiteley-mad-max-fury-road/|archivedate= 21 May 2015|df= dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSince 2010, she has been in a relationship with actor [[Jason Statham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/rosie-huntington-whiteley-direction-pose-glamour-article-1.1389347|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley cozies up to One Direction in Glamour: 'The lads are like puppies - they're adorable!'|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|location=New York City|date=3 July 2013|accessdate=3 July 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130706233621/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/rosie-huntington-whiteley-direction-pose-glamour-article-1.1389347|archivedate=6 July 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In January 2016, her representative confirmed they had become engaged.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/179703_rosie_huntington_whiteley_jason_statham_engaged_debut_ring_at_golden_globes/|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley & Jason Statham Are Engaged -- See the Ring She Debuted at Golden Globes!|first=Desiree|last=Murphy|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|date=10 January 2016|accessdate=13 March 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314160640/http://www.etonline.com/news/179703_rosie_huntington_whiteley_jason_statham_engaged_debut_ring_at_golden_globes/|archivedate=14 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On February 9, 2017, she announced that she was pregnant with the couple's first child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/rosie-huntington-whiteley-pregnant-jason-statham-expecting-first-child/|title=Jason Statham and Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Expecting First Child|date=9 February 2017|work=People|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170409223328/http://people.com/babies/rosie-huntington-whiteley-pregnant-jason-statham-expecting-first-child/|archivedate=9 April 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Their son was born in June that same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/jason-statham-rosie-huntington-whiteley-welcome-son-jack-oscar/|title=Jason Statham and Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Welcome Son Jack Oscar|date=28 June 2017|work=People|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628175808/http://people.com/babies/jason-statham-rosie-huntington-whiteley-welcome-son-jack-oscar/|archivedate=28 June 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/rosie-huntington-whiteley-baby-jack-oscar|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Gives Birth To Her First Son|last=Newbold|first=Alice|website=[[British Vogue]]|language=en-GB|date=28 June 2017|access-date=2019-10-10}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n\n|-\n\n| 2011\n|''[[Transformers: Dark of the Moon]]''\n|[[Carly Witwicky#Transformers Cinematic Universe|Carly Spencer]]\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]''\n| The Splendid Angharad\n|}\n\n== Accolades ==\n\nHuntington-Whiteley received [[Elle Style Awards|''Elle'' Style Award]]<nowiki/>s for 2009's \"Model of the Year,\" 2012's \"Top Style Icon\" and 2015's \"Model of the Year.\"<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.elleuk.com/star-style/news/node_326603#image=1|journal=Elle Magazine|title=The inside scoop from the Elle Style Awards 2009|date=10 February 2009|first=Claire|last=Sacre|accessdate=26 May 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113034952/http://www.elleuk.com/star-style/news/node_326603#image=1|archivedate=13 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"ELLE\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.elle.com/uk/fashion/celebrity-style/articles/a6307/the-rosie-huntington-whiteley-shoot/|title=The Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Shoot|date=2012-07-30|work=ELLE|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\"Evening Standard\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/rosie-huntington-whiteley-named-top-style-icon-at-elle-awards-7442867.html|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley named top style icon at Elle Awards|work=Evening Standard|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elle.com/uk/fashion/articles/a24845/rosie-huntington-whiteley-wins-model-of-the-year-2015/|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley wins Model Of The Year|date=2015-02-24|work=ELLE|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref>  In 2011, she was voted No. 1 in ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' Magazine's \"[[Maxim (magazine)#Maxim Hot 100|Hot 100]]\" list and received the \"Editor's Special Award\" at the [[Glamour Awards|''Glamour'' Awards]].<ref>{{cite journal| url=http://www.maxim.com/women/article/rosie-huntington-whiteley-hottest-woman-earth| journal=Maxim| title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley is the Hottest Woman on Earth| last=Maxim Staff| date=4 May 2011| accessdate=16 July 2015| url-status=live| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150717193507/http://www.maxim.com/women/article/rosie-huntington-whiteley-hottest-woman-earth| archivedate=17 July 2015| df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/article/glamour-award-winners|title=Full list of GLAMOUR 2011 Awards Winners|last=Glamour|access-date=2018-04-05}}</ref> At the ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'' Women of the Year Awards she was named 2014's \"Model of the Year\" and 2016's \"Businesswoman of the Year.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/people-parties/people-and-parties/news/g32471/harpers-bazaar-women-of-the-year-awards-2014/?slide=3|title=Harper's Bazaar Women of the Year Awards 2014|date=2014-11-05|work=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/culture/events/news/g37344/harpers-bazaar-women-of-the-year-2016-winners/|title=Women of the year 2016: Winners portfolio|date=2016-11-01|work=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nAs of July 2011, Huntington-Whiteley was ranked No. 15 on \"The Money Girls\" list and No. 3 on the \"Top 20 Sexiest Models\" list at models.com.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?model_id=4237#4237|title=The Money Girls|accessdate=16 July 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110802194329/http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?model_id=4237#4237|archivedate=2 August 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/sexiest/list.html?model_id=4237#4237|title=Top Sexiest Models|accessdate=16 July 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610173059/http://models.com/rankings/sexiest/list.html?model_id=4237#4237|archivedate=10 June 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/02/15/rosie-huntington-whiteley-elle-style-awards-dress/|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley Stuns In Sparkly Sheer Dress|publisher=Hollywood Life|date=15 February 2012|accessdate=16 July 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150717200129/http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/02/15/rosie-huntington-whiteley-elle-style-awards-dress/|archivedate=17 July 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> She was also voted No. 22 in [[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|''FHM'''s World's Sexiest Woman]] 2015 poll. In 2016 and 2017, Huntington-Whiteley appeared at #5 on Forbes' World's Highest Paid Models List with estimated earnings at $9 million and $9.5 million respectively.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/30/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-2016-karlie-kloss-and-kendall-jenner-storm-top-three-with-10-million-apiece/#2dc218082e17|title=The World's Highest-Paid Models 2016: Karlie Kloss And Kendall Jenner Storm Top Three With $10 Million Apiece|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|newspaper=Forbes|access-date=2016-10-13|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010060803/http://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/30/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-2016-karlie-kloss-and-kendall-jenner-storm-top-three-with-10-million-apiece/#2dc218082e17|archivedate=10 October 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/59f65cc231358e542c04644e/5-rosie-huntington-whitel/#457fc83724a7|title=Rosie Huntington-Whiteley - pg.10|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|website=Forbes|access-date=2018-04-05}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category \n! Nominated work\n! Result\n|-\n|2009\n|[[Elle Style Awards]]\n|Model of the Year<ref name=\"ELLE\"/>\n|<center> Herself</center>\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2011\n|[[Glamour Awards]]\n|Editor's Special Award<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/article/glamour-award-winners|title=Full list of GLAMOUR 2011 Awards Winners|last=Glamour|access-date=2018-04-05}}</ref>\n|<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Guys Choice]]\n| Our New Girlfriend\n||<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| CinemaCon Awards\n| Female Star of Tomorrow\n||<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[2011 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Movie Actress: Summer\n| rowspan=\"3\"| <center>''[[Transformers: Dark of the Moon]]''</center>\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2012\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[32nd Golden Raspberry Awards|Golden Raspberry Awards]]\n| [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Supporting Actress|Worst Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Screen Combo|Worst Screen Couple]] {{small|(shared with [[Shia LaBeouf]])}}\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[Elle Style Awards]]\n|Top Style Icon<ref name=\"Evening Standard\"/>\n|<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n|2014\n|Harper's Bazaar Women of the Year\n|Model of the Year<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/people-parties/people-and-parties/news/g32471/harpers-bazaar-women-of-the-year-awards-2014/?slide=3|title=Harper's Bazaar Women of the Year Awards 2014|date=2014-11-05|work=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n|2015\n|[[Elle Style Awards]]\n|Model of the Year<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elle.com/uk/fashion/articles/g24770/rosie-huntington-whiteley-model-of-the-year-2015/|title=#ELLEstyleawards 2015: RHW is Model of the Year|date=2015-02-19|work=ELLE|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2016\n|Harper's Bazaar Women of the Year\n|Businesswoman of the Year<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/culture/events/news/g37344/harpers-bazaar-women-of-the-year-2016-winners/|title=Women of the year 2016: Winners portfolio|date=2016-11-01|work=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2018-04-05|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|<center> Herself</center>\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| Gold Derby Awards\n| Best Ensemble Cast {{small|(shared with the cast)}}\n| <center>''[[Mad Max: Fury Road]]''</center>\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Huntington-Whiteley baronets]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Rankin Photography: ''Ten Times Rosie''. London: The Full Service, 2010. {{ISBN|978-0-9563-1555-7}}.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{IMDb name|2492819}}\n* [http://www.burkespeerage.com/ Rosie Huntington-Whiteley @ Burke's Peerage & Baronetage]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120903151007/http://eliteny.themode.net/div/elite/model/rosiehuntingtonwhitely/p/284/c/-1/?page=1 Rosie Huntington-Whiteley @ Elite New York City]\n\n{{Victoria's Secret Angels}}\n{{2000-2009VSFashion Show}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huntington-Whiteley, Rosie}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Tavistock]]\n[[Category:People connected with Tavistock]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Devon]]\n[[Category:English people of Polish-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:English female models]]\n[[Category:English film actresses]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:21st-century English actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Beverly Hills, California]]\n[[Category:English people of Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:Whiteley family|Rosie]]\n[[Category:Victoria's Secret Angels]]\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rosie_Huntington-Whiteley"}
